The paper deals with the problem of estimating and approximating edit distance, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of min-hash techniques for designing edit distance embeddings is also discussed. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.CC (computational complexity), and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). Among these, cs.DS and cs.IT seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with fundamental problems in these areas.
